          <Comment>For these reasons, this variant has been classified as Pathogenic. This variant disrupts a region of the ALDH7A1 protein in which other variant(s) (p.Arg519Lys) have been determined to be pathogenic (PMID: 23925287). This suggests that this is a clinically significant region of the protein, and that variants that disrupt it are likely to be disease-causing. This variant has not been reported in the literature in individuals affected with ALDH7A1-related conditions. This variant is not present in population databases (gnomAD no frequency). This sequence change creates a premature translational stop signal (p.Arg79Serfs*10) in the ALDH7A1 gene. While this is not anticipated to result in nonsense mediated decay, it is expected to disrupt the last 461 amino acid(s) of the ALDH7A1 protein.</Comment>
